Beginning June 15 and continuing through September 15, West Coast Airlines will be
Serving the heart of the famous Payette Lakes vacation area with a summer time stop
at McCall, Idaho. The mile-high Payette Lakes district is one of the most beautiful
spots in scenic Central Idaho ... lakes, heavy-timbered hills and mountains as
primitive as the day Lewis and Clark first saw Idaho.
Featured on the current timetable is Marilyn Evans of McCall,
Idaho with her fine catch of rainbow trout taken from the cold,
clear depths of the area's mountain waters.
More information and descriptive literature on the
area may be obtained from your travel agent or
local WCA office.
